title: 192A.07 RECEIVING PRISONERS.
text:
No provost marshal, commander of a guard, master at arms, warden, keeper, or officer of a city or county jail or any other jail, penitentiary, or prison designated under section 192A.065 may refuse to receive or keep any prisoner committed to the charge of that official or facility.
[Repealed by amendment, 2002 c 308 s 10]
